cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.NA, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper deals with missing data recovery in imaging and data science, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed regularization method involves solving a biharmonic equation, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and information theory (cs.IT). The experiments involve image inpainting, which is a topic in multimedia (cs.MM). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.NA, cs.IT, and cs.MM.
